---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Kitchen Tiling & Splashbacks Wellington | Rohullah Rassuli"
  description="Professional kitchen tiling and splashbacks in Wellington. Subway, mosaic, glass and large-format tiles. Transform your kitchen. Free quotes — call 021 026 02044."
  canonical="/services/kitchen-tiling"
  serviceName="Kitchen Tiling"
  serviceType="Kitchen Tiling"
  serviceDescription="Professional kitchen tiling and splashback installation in Wellington including subway tiles, mosaic, glass, and large-format porcelain."
>

  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split-layout fade-in-up">
        <div>
          <p class="lead">
            The kitchen is the heart of every Wellington home, and the right tiles can transform it from functional to stunning. Whether you need a striking splashback behind the hob, durable floor tiles that handle heavy foot traffic, or a feature wall that ties the whole room together, Rohullah Rassuli Tiling Services delivers kitchen tiling that looks exceptional and performs brilliantly.
          </p>
          <p>
            We work with homeowners, kitchen designers, and builders across the Wellington region to install tiles that complement cabinetry, benchtops, and appliances. From classic subway tiles in a Thorndon villa to bold geometric patterns in a modern Petone apartment, we bring precision and care to every kitchen tiling project.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
            <span>Kitchen splashback tiling project</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Kitchen Tiling Services -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Kitchen Tiling Services</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Expert tile installation for every surface in your kitchen.</p>

      <div class="services-grid">
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Kitchen Splashbacks</h3>
          <p>Protect the walls behind your benchtops, hob, and sink with a tiled splashback. We install everything from simple single-row splashbacks to full-height feature walls that run from benchtop to rangehood and beyond.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Kitchen Floor Tiling</h3>
          <p>Hard-wearing floor tiles that stand up to daily kitchen demands — spills, dropped utensils, and constant foot traffic. We ensure proper levelling and use slip-resistant finishes for safety.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Feature Walls</h3>
          <p>Create a focal point in your kitchen with a tiled feature wall. Textured tiles, bold patterns, or contrasting colours can define a dining nook, frame a window, or highlight an island bench.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Island Bench Cladding</h3>
          <p>Tile the sides of your kitchen island for a polished, contemporary look. Large-format tiles, stone-effect porcelain, or slim-profile panels create a seamless finish that is easy to clean.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Open-Plan Kitchen-Living Areas</h3>
          <p>When your kitchen flows into the living and dining space, consistent floor tiling ties the whole area together. We handle large open-plan layouts with careful attention to expansion joints and transitions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card fade-in-up">
          <h3>Butler's Pantry &amp; Scullery</h3>
          <p>Functional tile finishes for pantries and sculleries — splash-proof walls, easy-clean floors, and practical layouts designed for working spaces behind the main kitchen.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Popular Tile Styles -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Popular Kitchen Tile Styles</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Wellington homeowners love these trending tile styles for their kitchen projects.</p>

      <div class="services-grid fade-in-up">
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Subway Tiles</h3>
          <p>The timeless classic. Available in standard 75x150mm or elongated 75x300mm formats, subway tiles suit everything from heritage villas to modern minimalist kitchens. Lay them in brick bond, herringbone, or vertical stack for completely different looks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Mosaic Tiles</h3>
          <p>Small-format tiles on mesh backing that add texture, colour, and visual interest. Glass mosaics reflect light beautifully, while stone mosaics bring organic warmth. Perfect for splashbacks and feature strips.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Glass Tiles</h3>
          <p>Sleek, reflective, and easy to clean. Glass tiles are ideal for splashbacks where you want maximum light reflection. Available in a wide range of colours — from subtle neutrals to vibrant statement shades.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Large-Format Porcelain</h3>
          <p>Tiles over 600mm create a seamless, modern look with minimal grout lines. Stone-effect and concrete-effect porcelain is particularly popular in contemporary Wellington kitchens with clean-line cabinetry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Geometric &amp; Patterned Tiles</h3>
          <p>Hexagons, chevrons, fish scales, and Moroccan-inspired patterns make bold design statements. Use them as a splashback feature or to define a specific zone in an open-plan layout.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Handmade &amp; Artisan Tiles</h3>
          <p>Slightly irregular edges and glazes give handmade tiles a warm, characterful look that complements Wellington's many heritage homes. Each tile is unique, creating a one-of-a-kind finish.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Benefits Section -->
  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title--white">Why Tile Your Kitchen?</h2>
      <div class="services-grid">
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Durability</h3>
          <p>Quality tiles withstand heat, moisture, stains, and daily wear far better than paint or wallpaper. A professionally tiled splashback will look as good in ten years as it does on day one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Easy Cleaning</h3>
          <p>Glazed ceramic and porcelain tiles wipe clean in seconds. No special products needed — just a damp cloth to remove cooking splashes, grease, and everyday grime.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Heat Resistance</h3>
          <p>Tiles behind your hob and oven handle heat without discolouration or damage. Unlike acrylic or laminate splashbacks, tiles will not warp, melt, or yellow over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Added Property Value</h3>
          <p>A well-tiled kitchen is a strong selling point. Wellington buyers expect quality finishes, and professional tiling signals a home that has been maintained and upgraded with care.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Endless Design Options</h3>
          <p>With thousands of tile colours, sizes, textures, and patterns available, you can create a kitchen that is uniquely yours — from understated elegance to bold, statement-making design.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-card">
          <h3>Hygienic Surface</h3>
          <p>Non-porous glazed tiles do not harbour bacteria or absorb odours. This makes tiled surfaces the hygienic choice for food preparation areas and sink surrounds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Gallery Placeholder -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Kitchen Tiling Gallery</h2>
      <div class="services-grid fade-in-up">
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Subway tile splashback — Kelburn kitchen</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Large-format floor tiles — Petone open-plan</span>
        </div>
        <div class="image-placeholder image-placeholder--landscape">
          <span>Mosaic feature wall — Island Bay renovation</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Internal Links -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2 class="section-title section-title--left">Related Services</h2>
      <p>
        Kitchen tiling projects often involve <a href="/services/floor-tiling">floor tiling</a> that extends into adjoining living areas. If you are renovating the whole kitchen, you may also want <a href="/services/underfloor-heating">underfloor heating</a> installed beneath floor tiles for added comfort during Wellington's cooler months.
      </p>
      <p>
        Need to repair or update existing kitchen tiles? Our <a href="/services/tile-repairs">tile repair service</a> can replace cracked tiles, re-grout discoloured joints, and refresh your kitchen without a full renovation.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Contact us today</a> for a free kitchen tiling quote.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="section section--light">
    <div class="container fade-in-up">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions — Kitchen Tiling</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">What is the best tile for a kitchen splashback?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">Subway tiles, glass tiles, and porcelain tiles are all excellent choices for kitchen splashbacks. Subway tiles offer a timeless look, glass tiles are easy to clean and add a modern feel, and porcelain tiles come in endless patterns including marble-look finishes. We help you choose the right tile for your kitchen design and budget.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">How long does it take to tile a kitchen splashback?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">A kitchen splashback typically takes 1 to 2 days to complete, including surface preparation, tile installation, and grouting. Larger kitchens or complex mosaic patterns may take an additional day. We work efficiently to minimise disruption to your kitchen routine.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">Can you tile over existing kitchen tiles?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">In some cases, yes. If the existing tiles are firmly bonded, level, and in good condition, we can tile over them using a suitable adhesive. However, we always recommend removing old tiles for the best long-term result. We will assess your situation during our free quote visit and recommend the best approach.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">Do you supply the tiles or do I need to buy them?</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">You can supply your own tiles, or we can help you source them. We work closely with local Wellington tile suppliers and can recommend quality products that suit your style and budget. Either way, we will advise on the correct quantities to order, including a recommended allowance for cuts and waste.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best tile for a kitchen splashback?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Subway tiles, glass tiles, and porcelain tiles are all excellent choices for kitchen splashbacks. Subway tiles offer a timeless look, glass tiles are easy to clean and add a modern feel, and porcelain tiles come in endless patterns including marble-look finishes."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does it take to tile a kitchen splashback?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A kitchen splashback typically takes 1 to 2 days to complete, including surface preparation, tile installation, and grouting. Larger kitchens or complex mosaic patterns may take an additional day."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you tile over existing kitchen tiles?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "In some cases, yes. If the existing tiles are firmly bonded, level, and in good condition, we can tile over them using a suitable adhesive. However, we always recommend removing old tiles for the best long-term result."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do you supply the tiles or do I need to buy them?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You can supply your own tiles, or we can help you source them. We work closely with local Wellington tile suppliers and can recommend quality products that suit your style and budget."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

</ServiceLayout>

<script>
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in-up').forEach((el) => observer.observe(el));
</script>
